ally regular height. Most letters are c.75mm tall; O is consistently smaller than the other letters (55-60 mm), S taller at 95 mm, and the numeral 50 is 110 mm. A deep round interpunct is viisble at the end of line 3.",[44,52,57,62,68],{"type":45,"l":46,"from":47,"to":47,"h":48,"unit":49,"atLeast":50,"atMost":51},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","75-95","mm","75","95",{"type":45,"l":53,"from":54,"to":54,"h":55,"unit":49,"atLeast":56,"atMost":51},"Line 2","line2","55-95","55",{"type":45,"l":58,"from":59,"to":59,"h":60,"unit":49,"atLeast":61,"atMost":50},"Line 3","line3","60-75","60",{"type":45,"l":63,"from":64,"to":64,"h":65,"unit":49,"atLeast":66,"atMost":67},"Line 4","line4","70-110","70","110",{"type":69,"l":70,"from":47,"to":54,"unit":49},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":72,"notBefore":73,"notAfter":74},"252-248 BCE",-252,-248,[76],{"_":8,"type":77,"ref":78},"modern","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462323",[80],[81,82],37.7905564,13.3101399,[84,85],37.8054867,13.3542511,"Sicily",{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":89,"mainLang":90,"languages":91},"Latin","la",[89],"175816",{"n":94,"url":95,"height":96,"width":97,"desc":98,"surfaceType":99},"screen","ISic000610_tiled.tif","5520px","3680px","Photo J. Prag, 2023.10.28, courtesy Museo Civico di Corleone.","front",[101,104,106,108],{"atLeast":102,"atMost":103},75,95,{"atLeast":105,"atMost":103},55,{"atLeast":107,"atMost":102},60,{"atLeast":109,"atMost":110},70,110,[112,112,113,114,115,116,117,118,119,120],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Degrassi, 1965, ILLRP","Di Vita, 1955, Un milliarium del 252 a.C. e l'antica via Agrigento-Panormo","Degrassi, 1962, Nuovi miliari arcaici","Di Vita, 1963, Il miliario siciliano del console C. Aurelio Cotta","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Prag, 2006, Il miliario di Aurelius Cotta (ILLRP 1277): una lapide in contesto","Kreiler, 2011, Zwe